      <akn:section eId="sec_50_2206_57">
        <akn:num>50-2206.57</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Mandatory-minimum periods.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_50-2206_57_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A mandatory-minimum term of incarceration as provided in this subchapter shall be proven to the court by a preponderance of the evidence.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_50-2206_57_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A person sentenced for an offense under this subchapter may be subjected to multiple mandatory-minimum terms of incarceration. Each mandatory-minimum term of incarceration must be served consecutively, except that no combination of mandatory- minimum terms of incarceration shall exceed the maximum penalty for the offense, including any applicable enhancements.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
